        "subject": "LU-13500 ldlm: Do not LRU-cancel \"expensive\" locks for in bl-ast",
        "message": "LU-13500 ldlm: Do not LRU-cancel \"expensive\" locks for in bl-ast\n\nWhen we got a blocking ast that results in a lock cancel, we definitely\nshould avoid canceling lru locks that results in extra RPCs like\nPW locks with dirty data or OPEN locks that must send a CLOSE RPC\nfirst. Those RPCs might take a long time and what's worse, they might\nend up not being sent out at all because of lack of request slots.\n\nLustre-change: https://review.whamcloud.com/40602\n\nChange-Id: Ic2f016bb11ac085d11515f957f1825d34049d006\nSigned-off-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_12"
    }
  },
